Investigation of Lassa Fever in Nigeria: 2020-2025
Lassa fever is an acute viral haemorrhagic illness caused by Lassa virus, a member of the arenavirus family of viruses. Nigeria has the highest burden of Lassa fever cases in West Africa. Strengthening of capacity for lab diagnostics and case management in previous years resulted in greater case detection.
